{"type":"message","id":"21723a13","parentId":"eceea5ec","timestamp":"2026-04-30T15:26:52.653Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see exactly what happened in the 11:09 AM run. The cron job ran at 11:09 AM (15:09 UTC). It:\n\n1. Checked Gmail (4 new emails) - and sent a Gmail report\n2. Checked iCloud - found no new emails (all IDs ≤ 14, which was the last seen ID)\n3. But the cron job name says \"Gmail + iCloud\" and the session label says \"Cron: Emmy Email Check (Gmail + iCloud)\"\n\nThe cron job IS checking both accounts. But Bobby only got the iCloud message because Gmail had \"low priority\" emails and maybe it didn't send a separate message? Wait, looking at the transcript, it DID send the Gmail report (\"📬 **GMAIL — New Mail (4 new)**...\") and then separately sent \"📬 **ICLOUD — No new emails**\".\n \nSo both messages were sent to Telegram, but it's possible Gmail didn't send because all 4 emails were marked low priority and fell below some threshold, or maybe they were grouped with the iCloud report. Let me check the most recent run around 11:20 to see what the current state is.\n","thinkingSignature":"23450b2f0da8e2594e3b97da250a8162cf62c30826b97ea7c932060480e5c539"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fssc5b6ztunj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -lt ~/.openclaw/agents/emmy/sessions/*.jsonl 2>/dev/null | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2311,"output":297,"cacheRead":51008,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53616,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777562796451,"responseId":"0642a7acd357524b77fa58cdf020e001"}}
