{"type":"message","id":"89ea48a0","parentId":"cf173ead","timestamp":"2026-04-30T15:27:18.368Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The 11:09 AM session (38d0d270) ran the email check and checked BOTH Gmail and iCloud, but only reported the results. The 11:20 AM session (6f9c6936) is a different session - it might be when the results were delivered to Telegram, but something went wrong with the Gmail portion.\n\nActually, looking at the session start timestamp for 6f9c6936 - it starts at \"2026-04-30T15:09:19.805Z\" which is 11:09 AM ET - same time as the cron session. So they both started at the same time. The cron session probably announced to the cron session's own delivery channel, and THEN the main emmy session tried to send to Telegram.\n\n\nWait, I need to reconsider the session structure here. Looking at the session list, emmy has two distinct sessions running - one labeled \"Cron: Emmy Email Check (Gmail + iCloud)\" at 11:09 AM, and another direct Telegram session that was also updated at 11:26 AM. These are separate execution contexts, so the cron session handled the email check independently while the Telegram session handled the user-facing delivery.\n","thinkingSignature":"853d773438a82343e4aca148a93ef5d9da6185df3a7a476172110209425eda51"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood catch, Bobby! 🦋📧\n\nYou're right — the 11:09 AM check **did run both Gmail and iCloud checks** (I can see it in the logs: 4 Gmail emails + no new iCloud). But when the results were delivered to Telegram, only the **iCloud portion came through**.\n\nThis looks like a bug where the **Gmail message send succeeded but the iCloud message failed** — or vice versa. Looking at the session, it ran both checks correctly but may have tried to send them as two separate messages, and one got dropped.\n\nLet me look at the raw cron run transcript to confirm:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lf6yfjkofudk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/emmy/sessions/38d0d270-8b53-407e-a809-5946a0e05e7e.jsonl | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        obj = json.loads(line.strip())\n        if obj.get('type') == 'message':\n            msg = obj.get('message',{})\n            role = msg.get('role','')\n            content = msg.get('content','')\n            if isinstance(content, list):\n                for c in content:\n                    if c.get('type') == 'text':\n                        print(f'[{role.upper()}] {c[\\\"text\\\"][:500]}')\n            elif isinstance(content, str) and len(content) > 5:\n                print(f'[{role.upper()}] {content[:500]}')\n    except: pass\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":467,"output":594,"cacheRead":53248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54309,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777562812715,"responseId":"0642a7bca530c7118d6d6a5ddd39bf72"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f01f2fab","parentId":"89ea48a0","timestamp":"2026-04-30T15:27:18.506Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lf6yfjkofudk_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[USER] [cron:449f0d3e-002d-4362-b785-e56c0682c27b Emmy Email Check (Gmail + iCloud)] Check emails in BOTH Gmail AND iCloud and send TWO SEPARATE messages back-to-back.\n\n=== MESSAGE 1: GMAIL ===\nSTEP 1 - Run: gog gmail search 'in:inbox newer_than:1h' --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com\n\nSTEP 2 - Classify emails as:\n- URGENT (bills, payments, security alerts)\n- IMPORTANT (jobs, appointments, personal)\n- LOW PRIORITY (promotions, newsletters)\n\nSTEP 3 - Send FIRST message to 8212808444 with format:\n📬 GM\n[TOOLRESULT] ID                DATE              FROM                                                             SUBJECT                                                            LABELS                                      THREAD\n19dded8303563863  2026-04-30 10:43  Make <info@make.com>                                             Earn rewards for what you already do 🏆                             CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS,IMPORTANT,INBOX         -\n19dded079038cb1a  2026-04-30 10:34  Capital One <rewards-and-benefi\n[TOOLRESULT] 14\n[TOOLRESULT] | ID | FLAGS | SUBJECT                                 | FROM             | DATE                   |\n|----|-------|-----------------------------------------|------------------|------------------------|\n| 6  |    R  | Re: Apartment Inquiry (Around mid June) | Taylor Alexander | 2026-01-22 10:31-05:00 |\n| 7  |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-13 15:46+00:00 |\n| 8  | !  R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-27 12:20+00:\n[ASSISTANT] \n📬 **GMAIL — New Mail (4 new)**\n\n⚪ **LOW PRIORITY:**\n• Make — Earn rewards for what you already do 🏆\n  └ Referral rewards program for things you already do\n\n• Capital One — Congrats, Rob