{"type":"message","id":"38ec7348","parentId":"f01f2fab","timestamp":"2026-04-30T15:27:41.002Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the issue! The cron job prompt that was set up says \"Check emails in BOTH Gmail AND iCloud and send TWO SEPARATE messages back-to-back.\" But looking at the actual cron job run, it DID check both - Gmail had 4 new emails and iCloud had no new emails. So the system is working correctly.\n\nBut Bobby is saying he only got an iCloud email check at 11:09 and not a Gmail check. Let me look at what messages were actually delivered to Bobby around 11:09.\n\nLooking at the transcript, it sent:\n1. Gmail message with 4 new emails\n2. iCloud message \"No new emails\"\n \nWait, the timestamps are throwing me off - the cron run shows 11:09 AM but the emails in the inbox are dated 2026-04-30 10:43 and 10:34, which is earlier. And there's a 11:26 session that's only 3 minutes old, so the most recent run might be what I should be looking at instead. The real issue is probably that there was a Gmail check at 11:09 but Bobby never received the Telegram notification for it - the Gmail results just showed up as part of the session history, possibly because the announcement failed or the message format was incomplete.\n","thinkingSignature":"53d4bab33b4b0b10de0008d627aa2a390de14300c452c4f58eef764add1bd16c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tyuav2cf1e61_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/agents/emmy/sessions/38d0d270-8b53-407e-a809-5946a0e05e7e.jsonl | python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nfor line in sys.stdin:\n    try:\n        obj = json.loads(line.strip())\n        if obj.get('type') == 'message':\n            msg = obj.get('message',{})\n            role = msg.get('role','')\n            content = msg.get('content','')\n            if isinstance(content, list):\n                for c in content:\n                    if c.get('type') == 'toolCall' and c.get('name') == 'message':\n                        args = c.get('arguments',{})\n                        print(f'[MESSAGE TOOL] target:{args.get(\\\"target\\\")} action:{args.get(\\\"action\\\")} msg:{str(args.get(\\\"message\\\",\\\"\\\"))[:200]}')\n    except: pass\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":870,"output":494,"cacheRead":53632,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":54996,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777562838508,"responseId":"0642a7d6c13ccae497ea9f3365cb6fc3"}}
